author: Suhas Nayse
title: Rohan, Sudhanshu-Jaskaran enter State sub-junior badminton semis
text:
NAGPUR: Rohan Gurbani stormed into the U-15 boys singles semifinal in the Maharashtra Sub-Junior State Selection Badminton tournament at Ratnagiri on Friday. 

In the quarterfinal, top seed Rohan outclassed sixth seed Rahul Kane of Thane 21-17, 21-14 in just 24 minutes to book his place in the last four. 

Rohan, a student of Centre Point School, Katol Road, will take on Thane's Rohan Thool for a spot in the final on Saturday. 

Nagpur pair Sudhanshu Bhure and Jaskaran Suri also played well to enter the U-15 boys doubles semis. The unseeded pair shocked fourth seeds Parthiv Chhabria and Pranava Jain 21-15, 18-21, 21-19 in 45 minutes to advance. 

Sudhanshu-Jaskaran will now clash with Anay Apte and Parth Jategaonkar in the semis on Saturday.
